{"lemma":"بَعْلٌ","slug":"بَعْلٌ","root":"ب.ع.ل","root_slug":"ب-ع-ل","root_link":"/words/roots/ب-ع-ل","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"بَعْل","root":"بعل","pos":"N","occurrence_count":7},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":2,"pos_tags":["name","noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":4},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n2911"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%A8%D9%8E%D8%B9%D9%92%D9%84%D9%8C"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"husband","examples":[{"text":"وَإِنِ ٱمْرَأَةٌ خَافَتْ مِنْ بَعْلِهَا نُشُوزًا أَوْ إِعْرَاضًا فَلَا جُنَاحَ عَلَيْهِمَا أَنْ يُصْلِحَا بَيْنَهُمَا صُلْحًا ۚ وَٱلصُّلْحُ خَيْرٌ ۗ"}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"lord, master, owner, possessor","tags":["archaic"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"unirrigated land or plants thriving on a natural water supply","tags":["obsolete"]},{"pos":"name","gloss":"Baal","examples":[{"text":"أَتَدْعُونَ بَعْلًا وَتَذَرُونَ أَحْسَنَ الْخَالِقِينَ","english":"Do ye call upon ˹the idol of˺ Ba’l and abandon the Best of Creators—"}]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"From Proto-Semitic *baʕl-."},"ipa":["/baʕl/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n2911","headword_ar":"بَعْلٌ","root":"bEl","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A husband:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Mgh, Msb, K:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"buEuwlapN","text_ar":"بُعُولَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"buEuwlN","text_ar":"بُعُولٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"biEaAlN","text_ar":"بِعَالٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (K.) And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A wife;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baEolapN","text_ar":"بَعْلَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, Msb, K;) like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zawojN","text_ar":"زَوْجٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zawojapN","text_ar":"زَوْجَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S, Msb. *) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A lord, a master, an owner,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a possessor,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb, K,) of a thing, (K,) such as a house, and a beast, (TA,) or a she-camel: (S:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a head, chief, ruler,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"person of authority."},{"kind":"text","text":"(El-Khattábee, TA.) ―         -b3-  [And hence,]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A certain idol,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of gold,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"belonging to the people of Ilyás,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K,) who is said to be the same as Idrees, the grandfather, or an ancestor, of Noah, or to have been a grandson of Aaron, (Bd in vi. 85,) or the son of the brother of Aaron: (Jel ibid.:) it is mentioned in the Kur xxxvii. 123: accord. to one copy of the K,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it belonged to the people of Jonas;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and so in the Kitáb el-Mujarrad of Kr: accord. to Mujáhid, it means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a deity that is not God:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a certain king:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAar, K:) but [SM says,] the correct explanation is the first: (TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a certain idol belonging to the people of Bekk, in Syria;"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the town now called Baala-Bekk:"},{"kind":"text","text":"so in the Kur: (Bd, Jel: *) or it means in the dial. of El-Yemen"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a lord;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and so in the Kur. (Bd.) ―         -b4-  Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"One whom it is a necessary duty to obey;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a father,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a mother,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the like."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b5-  And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A family,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"household, whose maintenance is incumbent on a man."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b6-  And it may be a contraction of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baEilN","text_ar":"بَعِلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", as meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Lacking strength,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"power,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"ability; unable to find the right way to accomplish his affair."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b7-  Also (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A weight,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"burden."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA.) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aSobaHa fulaAnN baEolFA EalaY A^aholihi","text_ar":"اَصْبَحَ فُلَانٌ بَعْلًا عَلَى اَهْلِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Such a one became a weight,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"burden, upon his family;"},{"kind":"text","text":"because of his ascendency over them. (Er-Rághib, TA.) ―         -b8-  (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Elevated land,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"upon which comes neither running water nor torrent,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that is not rained upon more than once in the year:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) or (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"land elevated above other land;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as being likened to the man who is thus termed. (Er-Rághib, TA.) ―         -b9-  (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Any palm-trees,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"other trees,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"seed-produce, not watered:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"such as are watered by the rain:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) or (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"palm-trees"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naxol","text_ar":"نَخْل"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that imbibe with their roots, and so need not to be watered:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Mgh, Msb, K:) metaphorically so applied: (Mgh:) AA says that it is"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"syn. with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ei*oYN","text_ar":"عِذْىٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"what is watered by the rain:"},{"kind":"text","text":"but As says that this latter word has the meaning just given, whereas"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bEl","text_ar":"بعل"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"what imbibes with its roots, without irrigation or rain:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"palm-trees growing in land whereof the supply of water is near"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to the surface"},{"kind":"text","text":"],"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"so that it suffices without their having irrigation or rain:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"large, so as to imbibe with the roots:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Er-Rághib, TA:) and (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a male palm-tree;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA;) likened to the man who is thus termed: (TA:) and Az says that it is used as meaning (assumed tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"dates such as are termed"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qasob","text_ar":"قَسْب"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) ―         -b10-  And (assumed tropical:)  The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tax,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"impost, that is given for the watering of palm-trees."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.)"}],"source_refs":["S","Mgh","Msb","K","TA","IAar"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}